Dr. '''John Coffey''' is an English historian.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www2.le.ac.uk/departments/history/people/jcoffey | title=Professor John Coffey | accessdate=2013-08-13}}</ref> He has written monographs on [[Samuel Rutherford]] and [[John Goodwin (preacher)|John Goodwin]], and is Professor of early modern history at the [[University of Leicester]]. His ''Persecution and Toleration in Protestant England, 1558–1689'' is the first overview work on the topic since [[Wilbur Kitchener Jordan|W.K. Jordan's]] 4-volume work ''The Development of Religious Toleration in England'' (1932–1940).

==Recent Publications==
